In this press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Hogan Gidley discusses President Trump's upcoming speech at the American Farm Bureau and the release of a rural prosperity task force report. Gidley also comments on Steve Bannon's recent statement expressing regret for his comments in the Michael Wolff book, stating that there is no way back for Bannon. He also addresses questions about Jared Kushner and Ivanka Trump's role in the White House, the President's views on Jeff Sessions' recusal from the Russia investigation, and the possibility of the President sitting for an interview with the Special Counsel. Gidley also comments on Oprah Winfrey's speech at the Golden Globes, the President's work schedule, and the President's decision on Iran sanctions. He concludes by addressing the President's recent tweet about being a "stable genius" and dismissing claims of his mental stability.